{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, a schedule that reduces tardiness but not resource utilization may not be optimal.",
    "In contrast, the use of a multi-objective function with multiple performance measures provides a more holistic approach to the problem and permits a thorough evaluation of scheduling solutions.",
    "Furthermore, the obtained solutions would strike a balance that accounts for the inherent trade-offs between objectives.",
    "However, this makes the problem more complicated and may necessitate the application of more sophisticated optimization techniques.",
    "Various techniques, such as Pareto-optimality, can be utilized to identify a group of non-dominated schedules."
  ]
}